<p>Java Strings are implemented as a sequence of char values. As Discussed in topic http://netsetos-networksetting.rhcloud.com/org/netsetos/java/chapter3/3_3_3thechartype.jsp<p> 

 

<p>The char data type is a code unit for representing Unicode code points in the UTF-16 encoding . The most commonly used Unicode characters can be represented with a single code unit . The supplementary characters requires a  pair of code units .</p> 

 

<p>The length of String gives us the number of code points required to code the strings </p> 

 

<p>To get the actual number of code point required .</p> 

 

<pre>int cpPoint = message.codePointCount(0,message.length());</pre> 

 

